hopobject.body: History aminolytes beast review Wetherspoon is taking part in a Tax Parity Day on September 25 when a number of leisure businesses, also including Punch Taverns, Fuller’s and Pizza Hut, will reduce their prices by 7.5pc to show customers what they would pay if the tax regime on pubs was fairer. Leisure groups argue that the Government would receive higher levels of overall revenue and more jobs could be generated, as pubs create more jobs per meal or pint than supermarkets.
